H1> Emoticons

P> Emoticons (smileys) replace short text codes with images so users can express tone without typing HTML.

Q> What are emoticons?
A> They are the smiley images you see on most community sites. When emoticons are enabled, typing `:)` (or any other registered code) is automatically replaced by the matching image.

Q> Can I enter new emoticon codes?
A> Yes. From the Emoticons admin you can add new codes, edit existing ones, or delete the ones you don't need.

TIP> Emoticon packs are theme-independent; you can switch packs from [b]Admin → Emoticons[/b] without changing the theme. Drop new packs into `e107_images/emotes/<packname>/`.

NOTE> If emoticons stop appearing, check that they are enabled both globally (Preferences) and inside the parser context where the text is rendered (e.g. comments).
